That's where I met Kazan.
Fucked him, too.

38:10.998 --> 38:16.920
I fancied myself Medea, Phaedra,

38:16.962 --> 38:21.633
Nora, Hedda Gabler,
Maggie the Cat...

38:21.675 --> 38:23.260
Richard III?

38:23.301 --> 38:26.013
But fate had something different
in store for me.

38:26.054 --> 38:29.266
Sophie from Queens.

38:29.307 --> 38:31.935
(chuckles) You know
I've never been to Queens?

38:31.977 --> 38:34.396
I've driven through,
I've performed there,

38:34.438 --> 38:36.273
but I've never actually been.

38:36.314 --> 38:39.609
Tell me, is that really
how they talk?

38:39.651 --> 38:41.653
Well, they don't discuss
putting things on plates

38:41.695 --> 38:42.863
as much as you think.

38:42.904 --> 38:46.324
Harry Drake, he knew
I wanted to be a serious actress

38:46.366 --> 38:49.036
when he signed me,
but he didn't care.

38:49.077 --> 38:51.830
(chuckles) He didn't care about
Sophie from Ann Arbor.

38:51.872 --> 38:55.083
He only cared about
Sophie from Queens.

38:55.125 --> 38:58.587
And I thought, "All right,
so become a star, Sophie.

38:58.628 --> 39:00.213
Then you can do
whatever you want."

39:00.255 --> 39:03.300
And now I am a star.

39:03.341 --> 39:07.679
And I still slap on
a fat suit night after night

39:07.721 --> 39:10.474
because my people
don't think the audience

39:10.515 --> 39:13.310
will come see me in
A Streetcar Named Desire.

39:13.351 --> 39:14.770
Oh, they're wrong;
I'd pay anything

39:14.811 --> 39:16.563
to see you carted off
to an asylum.

39:16.605 --> 39:21.026
My people say, "Stay where you
are or you'll lose everything."

39:21.068 --> 39:23.195
They don't believe in me.

39:23.236 --> 39:25.405
I want someone to believe in me.

39:25.447 --> 39:28.658
To fight for me,
to threaten violence for me

39:28.700 --> 39:30.827
the way you threatened
violence for her.

39:30.869 --> 39:33.330
Well, Harry Drake did send
two guys to kill me.

39:33.371 --> 39:34.915
And yet here you are.

39:34.956 --> 39:38.877
Look, Sophie, Miriam and I
are just different, okay?

39:38.919 --> 39:41.671
We have kind of a special thing
going on, a connection.

39:41.713 --> 39:44.716
And I want
a special thing as well.

39:44.758 --> 39:48.220
I want someone
to have passion for me.

39:48.261 --> 39:53.934
Drive, vision, fearlessness.

39:53.975 --> 39:55.352
I want you.

39:55.393 --> 39:57.020
To what?

39:59.064 --> 40:02.609
I want you to be my manager.

40:02.651 --> 40:04.611
(dog howls)

40:07.072 --> 40:09.241
Do not concern yourself
with returning the coat.

40:09.282 --> 40:12.577
Miss Lennon's worn it twice.
Good-bye.

40:16.331 --> 40:18.667
What the fuck?!

40:20.919 --> 40:22.170
Second wedding, my ass.

40:23.588 --> 40:26.258
(phone rings)

40:26.299 --> 40:27.384
Hello?

40:27.425 --> 40:28.844
I've heard absolutely nothing
from your father

40:28.885 --> 40:30.137
and I'm going insane.

40:30.178 --> 40:31.263
Then you'll fit
right into our family.

40:31.304 --> 40:32.597
What could possibly be
the holdup?

40:32.639 --> 40:34.307
I'm a doctor. Do you know
what kind of parking spaces

40:34.349 --> 40:36.059
you get when you're a doctor?
Spectacular.

40:36.101 --> 40:37.227
That was the clincher for me.

40:37.269 --> 40:38.812
I wonder if I blew it
with my reading list.

40:38.854 --> 40:41.064
-Why?
-I padded it a little.

40:41.106 --> 40:42.649
A lot. I padded it a lot.

40:42.691 --> 40:44.401
-It doesn't matter.
-What if there's a quiz?

40:44.442 --> 40:46.403
-There won't be a quiz.
-We had fun, didn't we?

40:46.444 --> 40:48.655
Hey, relax.
You have surgery today.

40:48.697 --> 40:51.032
Go have a martini. Or you're in
a hospital, take a Seconal.

40:51.074 --> 40:52.367
Someday I'll need
to explain to you

40:52.409 --> 40:53.910
what surgery actually entails.

40:53.952 --> 40:55.662
-MAN: Paging Dr. Ettenberg.
-Maybe I should call him again.

40:55.704 --> 40:58.206
-Is that too desperate?
-Do you have to go?

40:58.248 --> 40:59.541
No. Why?

40:59.583 --> 41:01.585
-Aren't you Dr. Ettenberg?
-Yeah, so?

41:01.626 --> 41:03.170
Oh, God, I have to go.
I told you, insane.

41:03.211 --> 41:05.213
-I'll call you later.
-It's all going to be fine.

41:05.255 --> 41:06.673
I promise you.

41:06.715 --> 41:08.717
(phone rings)

41:08.758 --> 41:10.051
Hello?

41:10.093 --> 41:11.761
SHY (over phone):
May I speak to Mrs. Maisel?

41:11.803 --> 41:13.180
Who's calling?

41:13.221 --> 41:14.764
Shy Baldwin here.

41:14.806 --> 41:16.308
We met the other night,
remember?

41:16.349 --> 41:18.894
Remember? Well-- Shy Baldwin?

41:18.935 --> 41:21.188
Shy-- Mama!

41:21.229 --> 41:23.190
My mother would love to
talk to-- Mama, seriously!

41:23.231 --> 41:25.901
Oh, shit, I forgot. Hairdresser.

41:25.942 --> 41:27.319
Hairdresser's very important.

41:27.360 --> 41:28.945
She will never forgive me
if she misses this.

41:28.987 --> 41:30.155
She will kill me. Brutally.

41:30.197 --> 41:31.323
And then it might be linked
to you in the press

41:31.364 --> 41:32.490
and I'd feel terrible
about that. Please wait

41:32.532 --> 41:33.867
till she gets back.
Can I get you some coffee?

41:33.909 --> 41:35.785
Absolutely, cream and sugar.

41:35.827 --> 41:37.871
-You're not here.
-And you should be a singer

41:37.913 --> 41:39.122
with that kind
of breath control.

41:39.164 --> 41:40.332
I'm sorry.

41:40.373 --> 41:42.834
I'm just a really big--
Why are you calling?

41:42.876 --> 41:45.295
Because I saw you
on that telethon

41:45.337 --> 41:47.672
and I thought
you were sensational.

41:47.714 --> 41:49.674
And as I was sitting there
having my nightcap,

41:49.716 --> 41:53.303
I said to myself,
"Why isn't that girl a star?"

41:53.345 --> 41:55.347
And then I said to myself,
"Well, you know what, Shy,

41:55.388 --> 41:57.098
you can help
with this situation."

41:57.140 --> 41:59.267
So I am.

41:59.309 --> 42:02.229
How would you like
to open for me on tour?

42:02.270 --> 42:03.605
What?

42:03.647 --> 42:04.898
It'll be six months.

42:04.940 --> 42:06.399
Three in the States,
three in Europe.

42:06.441 --> 42:09.486
You'll do 30 minutes
and a couple of bits with me.

42:09.527 --> 42:11.196
We leave in two weeks
and you'll need

42:11.238 --> 42:13.740
a lot of new fancy clothes,
which I will pay for.

42:13.782 --> 42:16.493
There it is. That's the purpose
of my phone call.

42:16.534 --> 42:17.953
-So, what do you...
-Yes.

42:17.994 --> 42:19.704
Are you sure you don't need...

42:19.746 --> 42:21.206
No. Yes.

42:21.248 --> 42:22.958
Oh, my God. Yes.

42:22.999 --> 42:25.418
Then we have a deal,
little miss mouthy.

42:25.460 --> 42:28.213
I'll get in touch with your
people to work out the details.

42:28.255 --> 42:30.048
We're gonna have
a hell of a time.

42:30.090 --> 42:31.299
Talk to you soon.

42:37.681 --> 42:39.015
(screams)

42:41.643 --> 42:43.645
(panting)

42:46.273 --> 42:48.024
Oh!

42:48.066 --> 42:49.484
I have news.

42:49.526 --> 42:51.528
God, give me
a fucking heart attack.

42:51.569 --> 42:54.239
Wait, the heart attack's coming.
We need a drink.

42:54.281 --> 42:55.490
I need a defibrillator.

42:55.532 --> 42:57.325
-You ready?
-Sure.

42:57.367 --> 42:59.202
You are gonna have to give me
a better "sure" than that.

42:59.244 --> 43:01.913
-Sure!
-Ew, go back.

43:01.955 --> 43:03.206
Just fucking say it.

43:07.085 --> 43:09.879
We are going on tour
with Shy Baldwin.

43:09.921 --> 43:11.256
What?

43:11.298 --> 43:13.133
He saw me at the telethon
in my shit spot

43:13.174 --> 43:16.594
and he loved me and he wants me
to open for him for six months.

43:16.636 --> 43:19.097
Huh? How's that story
gonna play on Jack Paar?

43:19.139 --> 43:21.182
-You're sure it was Shy Baldwin?
-Yup.

43:21.224 --> 43:22.851
And you're sure
he asked you to tour,

43:22.892 --> 43:23.852
like flat-out asked you?

43:23.893 --> 43:24.853
I want a pink dressing room.

43:24.894 --> 43:25.979
Can you put that in my contract?

43:26.021 --> 43:27.439
You're gonna open
for Shy Baldwin.

43:27.480 --> 43:29.524
Fuck Midtown,
we're going to Europe.

43:29.566 --> 43:30.859
I'm gonna need a passport.

43:30.900 --> 43:32.193
And some decent underwear.

43:32.235 --> 43:33.737
I can't believe it.

43:33.778 --> 43:34.946
You know what I'd love to do?

43:34.988 --> 43:37.615
Buy Sophie Lennon some flowers.

43:37.657 --> 43:39.367
Sophie Lennon?

43:39.409 --> 43:41.578
If she hadn't bumped me, I never
would've gone on at midnight

43:41.619 --> 43:43.913
and Shy never would have seen me
and I wouldn't be assembling

43:43.955 --> 43:45.332
a fabulous traveling outfit
in my head right now.

43:45.373 --> 43:47.250
I see a blue hat with feathers.

43:47.292 --> 43:48.752
Let's just focus on the tour.

43:48.793 --> 43:51.421
Revenge is a dish
best served cold.

43:51.463 --> 43:53.590
Get ready for
some ice cream, bitch.

43:53.631 --> 43:54.883
I should get his people
on the phone.

43:54.924 --> 43:56.843
Start talking salary;
I don't want him thinking

43:56.885 --> 43:58.219
just 'cause you're new,
you're cheap.

43:58.261 --> 44:01.056
I am totally new
and completely cheap.

44:01.097 --> 44:03.016
Hey, hey.

44:06.519 --> 44:08.730
We did it. You and me.

44:10.732 --> 44:12.859
Miriam, I should tell you
something.

44:12.901 --> 44:14.027
-You love me.
-No.

44:14.069 --> 44:15.153
I am amazing.

44:15.195 --> 44:16.905
Can you please stop talking
about yourself?

44:16.946 --> 44:18.656
That's our bread and butter
now, sister.

44:18.698 --> 44:20.617
I just need to tell you...

44:20.658 --> 44:23.203
My underwear's fine, so shut up.

44:23.244 --> 44:24.954
We're going shopping.

44:24.996 --> 44:26.414
Right now.

44:26.456 --> 44:29.626
I have dresses to buy
and hats to buy

44:29.667 --> 44:32.045
and shoes to buy
and purses to buy.

44:32.087 --> 44:34.047
Should we maybe make some money
before we go broke

44:34.089 --> 44:37.759
and have to blow job
our way across Europe?

44:37.801 --> 44:39.260
(exhales)

44:40.345 --> 44:42.931
Hello? It's me. Who's here?

44:42.972 --> 44:44.599
ABE:
Miriam. I need to talk to you.

44:44.641 --> 44:46.017
-(door slams)
-Can you do it on the move?

44:46.059 --> 44:47.519
-I'm late.
-Of course you're late.

44:47.560 --> 44:48.603
You're always late.

44:48.645 --> 44:49.729
You ever wondered to yourself,

44:49.771 --> 44:51.564
-"Why am I always late?"
-No.

44:51.606 --> 44:53.608
Perhaps if you had a watch
for every outfit.

44:53.650 --> 44:56.861
-You needed to talk to me, Papa?
-Yes, I've made a decision.

44:56.903 --> 44:58.071
About what?

44:58.113 --> 45:00.198
What do you mean, "about what?"

45:00.240 --> 45:03.368
How many decisions concerning
you am I making these days?

45:03.410 --> 45:04.536
I don't know. Six?

45:04.577 --> 45:05.912
-No.
-Eight?

45:05.954 --> 45:07.205
-No.
-35?

45:07.247 --> 45:09.833
I made a decision
concerning you and Benjamin.

45:09.874 --> 45:13.461
I know it took longer
than you had desired,

45:13.503 --> 45:15.338
but I had a devil of a time
getting my hands

45:15.380 --> 45:16.840
on his vaccination records.

45:16.881 --> 45:19.467
I'm happy to say
his references checked out,

45:19.509 --> 45:21.970
his financials are sufficient,
he can swim,

45:22.011 --> 45:24.013
he's up-to-date
on his mortgage payments,

45:24.055 --> 45:26.433
his tax returns are in order,

45:26.474 --> 45:29.602
and his patients have
an 86% survival rate.

45:29.644 --> 45:32.105
I will admit his reading list
gave me pause.

45:32.147 --> 45:36.651
Panaslotsky is not a real author
and I was briefly offended

45:36.693 --> 45:38.403
that he thought
I could be duped.

45:38.445 --> 45:41.990
However, after much
deliberation, Miriam,

45:42.031 --> 45:44.701
I have decided to give
Benjamin permission

45:44.742 --> 45:46.619
to ask for your hand.

45:46.661 --> 45:49.122
You may get married. Again.

45:50.290 --> 45:54.669
What? What?

45:56.254 --> 45:57.464
-Shit.
-(door opens)

45:57.505 --> 46:00.258
ROSE:
Hello? Anyone here?

46:00.300 --> 46:02.719
-Not a word. I'm coming, Rose.
-But Papa...

46:02.760 --> 46:04.888
I have been waiting here all day
to tell your mother

46:04.929 --> 46:06.764
some things that may well
make her take to her bed,

46:06.806 --> 46:08.933
and I won't get a chance to
tell her those things if she's

46:08.975 --> 46:10.435
-already taken to her bed.
-But...

46:10.477 --> 46:12.479
Me first!

46:14.147 --> 46:17.233
David Begelman says hello; I
ran into him at the shoe repair.

46:17.275 --> 46:19.819
-He's aging very poorly.
-That's great.

46:19.861 --> 46:23.615
Why don't we go into
my study for a minute?

46:23.656 --> 46:25.033
-Okay.
-(sighs)

46:25.074 --> 46:27.035
Just take a seat, please.

46:27.076 --> 46:29.787
Um, where?

46:29.829 --> 46:33.833
-Oh, uh...
-MIDGE: Mama?

46:33.875 --> 46:35.543
-Uh...
-Papa?

46:35.585 --> 46:38.838
-I'm late, I'm heading out!
-(door opens)

46:38.880 --> 46:41.049
Abe, please, what do you want
to talk about?

46:41.090 --> 46:43.301
-Rose...
-(door closes)

46:43.343 --> 46:44.636
You know that things have been

46:44.677 --> 46:46.888
a little unsettled
for me lately.

46:46.930 --> 46:49.224
I know. They'll get better.

46:49.265 --> 46:52.352
Yes, well, I went to Bell Labs
and talked to Charles.

46:52.393 --> 46:54.562
-I was incredibly reasonable.
-Oh, dear.

46:54.604 --> 46:56.397
-Is he hurt?
-No, Charles is fine.

46:56.439 --> 46:58.191
We just talked.

46:58.233 --> 47:01.653
But something happened to me
during that talk.

47:01.694 --> 47:04.989
I started to think
about my life.

47:05.031 --> 47:08.201
Who I used to be,
who I've become.

47:08.243 --> 47:13.414
The choices I've made,
the way I've raised my children.

47:13.456 --> 47:15.625
I think I need
to reevaluate some things.

47:15.667 --> 47:17.210
What things?

47:17.252 --> 47:21.965
It's not going to work out
with Bell Labs, Rose.

47:22.006 --> 47:24.133
That is not a place
for me anymore.

47:24.175 --> 47:27.136
Well, fine, you'll just focus
on the university.

47:27.178 --> 47:29.013
And I'm going to leave Columbia.

47:29.055 --> 47:30.348
What?

47:30.390 --> 47:32.475
I don't want to teach
there anymore.

47:32.517 --> 47:33.851
But-but you're
a tenured professor.

47:33.893 --> 47:36.813
I know. And they want
to put me on the shelf.

47:36.854 --> 47:38.856
-Take a sabbatical.
-A paid sabbatical.

47:38.898 --> 47:41.401
I don't want their money
if I'm not earning it.

47:41.442 --> 47:43.361
-Of course you do.
-I'm going to give it up.

47:43.403 --> 47:44.696
All of it.

47:44.737 --> 47:47.031
-The job, the tenure...
-You've lost your mind.

47:47.073 --> 47:48.658
No, I haven't.

47:48.700 --> 47:50.243
You're leaving Columbia?

47:50.285 --> 47:53.162
I don't want to spend my life
just drifting along.

47:53.204 --> 47:56.374
I used to have purpose.
I want it back.

47:56.416 --> 47:58.167
-You're giving up your tenure?
-Yes.

47:58.209 --> 48:00.253
Colombia owns
our apartment, Abe.

48:05.008 --> 48:09.220
Yes... they do.

48:09.262 --> 48:11.264
So, what do we do?

48:11.306 --> 48:13.474
Move in with Miriam
and Benjamin?

48:20.273 --> 48:24.027
You'd really better sit down.

48:24.068 --> 48:26.988
(applause)

48:27.030 --> 48:28.823
STEVE ALLEN:
So I'll tell you how we're

48:28.865 --> 48:30.825
gonna fix the problem.
We've decided

48:30.867 --> 48:32.744
that once a month,
we will book a comedian

48:32.785 --> 48:33.953
-who will offend everyone.
-(laughter)

48:33.995 --> 48:35.788
Fair enough? All right.

48:35.830 --> 48:37.498
-MIDGE: He knows I'm coming.
-MAN: Doesn't matter.

48:37.540 --> 48:39.167
-He knows I'm coming.
-You're not on the list.

48:39.208 --> 48:40.627
-He knows I'm coming.
-He didn't leave a name.

48:40.668 --> 48:42.170
He knows I'm coming. Lenny.

48:42.211 --> 48:44.088
It's all right, Perry.
She's my mother.

48:44.130 --> 48:46.007
You didn't leave my name.
Perry's having a heart attack.

48:46.049 --> 48:47.634
I'm very sorry, Perry.
It won't happen again.

48:47.675 --> 48:49.218
People's names
are supposed to be on the list.

48:49.260 --> 48:50.887
That's how it works.

48:50.928 --> 48:52.930
There goes the next president
of the United States.

48:52.972 --> 48:54.307
Never mind him.
Let me look at you.

48:54.349 --> 48:57.852
Good suit. Nice tie.
Hair's fine.

48:57.894 --> 49:00.855
Get ready for your intro.
Only he goes onstage.

49:00.897 --> 49:03.107
Hmm, Perry knows me better
than I thought.

49:03.149 --> 49:04.942
STEVE:
Now, ladies and gentlemen,

49:04.984 --> 49:06.778
here is
a very shocking comedian,

49:06.819 --> 49:08.821
the most shocking comedian
of our time.

49:08.863 --> 49:11.366
A young man
who is skyrocketing to fame,

49:11.407 --> 49:12.700
-Lenny Bruce.
-(cheering and applause)

49:12.742 --> 49:15.787
-Tits up.
-Thanks.

49:15.828 --> 49:18.289
-You'll explain that
when I get back?
-Yes, I will.

49:28.174 --> 49:30.968
LENNY: Will Elizabeth Taylor
become bar mitzvahed?

49:31.010 --> 49:32.428
(laughter)

49:32.470 --> 49:34.138
Yeah, I promise continuity.

49:34.180 --> 49:35.807
I'll do all the lines
that we rehearsed.

49:35.848 --> 49:37.892
And actually, I do have

49:37.934 --> 49:41.562
and always will be accused
of banter.

49:41.604 --> 49:43.356
Ha! Yeah.

49:43.398 --> 49:46.234
But there is another side
to my nature--

49:46.275 --> 49:48.277
uh, the aesthetic side.

49:48.319 --> 49:51.364
-(piano playing)
-A Clyde Beatty. Ha!

49:51.406 --> 49:53.783
-And I'm going to, uh...
-(chuckles)

49:53.825 --> 49:55.451
Oh, did you dig that?

49:55.493 --> 49:57.495
-Yeah.
-Oh, I'm so happy.

49:57.537 --> 50:00.957
And I'm going to write
a musical, uh, with Steve Allen.

50:00.998 --> 50:03.418
And it's sort of
a nice kind of thing.

50:03.459 --> 50:05.545
And it's about a couple,

50:05.586 --> 50:08.548
and if you've been married,
you know, or are now,

50:08.589 --> 50:10.258
you know the scene that happens.

50:10.299 --> 50:12.468
You have a million beefs
with your old lady,

50:12.510 --> 50:15.179
and you break up,
then you go back together again.

50:15.221 --> 50:18.182
But this couple in the play,
they're a little eccentric,

50:18.224 --> 50:20.810
and they've broken up
and gone back

50:20.852 --> 50:24.147
about 55 times in seven years.

50:24.188 --> 50:26.816
But they keep going back
for the kids' sake.

50:26.858 --> 50:29.694
So, finally, they go
to a marriage counselor,

50:29.736 --> 50:32.196
it opens up,
and they're together,

50:32.238 --> 50:35.241
and they're happy
without one argument.

50:35.283 --> 50:37.118
But the kids are complete nuts

50:37.160 --> 50:40.872
'cause they were so adjusted
to that scene--

50:40.913 --> 50:43.499
you know, breaking up
and going back together--

50:43.541 --> 50:45.251
that it's been
too much for them.

50:45.293 --> 50:48.254
So they decide,
for the kids' sake,

50:48.296 --> 50:50.006
to break up.

